A quadriplegic father made his daughter’s wedding day this weekend when he walked her down the aisle.

Augie Nieto, 56, who was diagnosed with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), a neurodegenerative disease, nearly a decade ago, was on hand to give away his youngest daughter, Lindsay, in Rancho Palos Verdes, California, Saturday.

Mr Nieto was diagnosed with the disease in 2005, and lost the use of his arms and legs within three years. A few years ago, he underwent a tracheotomy that left him unable to speak.

